However, we can modify the formula with affecting the product by multiplying assets/assets.

$$ \begin{aligned} 
ROE  & = \frac{\text{Net Income}}{\text{Total Equity}} \cdot \frac{\text{Assets}}{\text{Assets}} \\[25pt]
& = \frac{\text{Net Income}}{\text{Assets}} \cdot \frac{\text{Assets}}{\text{Total Equity}} 
\end{aligned}$$

Notice that with this we also calculated the **Equity Multiplier** since be stated that it can be calculated as:

$$ \begin{aligned} 
\text{Equity Multiplier} & = 1 +  \text{Debt-Equity Ratio} \\[15pt]
& = \boxed{1.57}
\end{aligned}$$


The Equity Multiplier is **1.57**
